Earlier this afternoon, the Sports, Arts and Culture Minister Nathi Mthethwa, along with the chairmen of Kaizer Chiefs and Orlando Pirates, donated masks and gloves to the National Institute of Communicable Diseases. The Minister, accompanied by Kaizer Motaung and Irvin Khoza, have made their way to Multichoice offices, where they will provide further details. JOHANNESBURG - Government and the football fraternity will host a joint media briefing on COVID-19 at the Multichoice headquarters. Minister of Health Dr Zweli Mkhize, Minister of Sports, Arts and Culture Nathi Mthethwa, chairmen of Kaizer Chiefs and Orlando Pirates and the Multichoice leadership will make an announcement at the news conference. Mthethwa, Kaizer Motaung and Irvin Khoza visited the offices of the National Institute for Communicable Diseases on Thursday afternoon. They donated masks and gloves to help fight the coronavirus. READ:Â COVID-19 travel ban: South Africans stuck in 'paradise' The number of confirmed positive COVID-19 cases in South Africa now stands at 2,415. There have been no new deaths reported. The number of coronavirus tests concluded to date is 87,022.  The Sports, Arts and Culture Minister, and the chairmen of Kaizer Chiefs and Orlando Pirates, are currently visiting the offices of the National Institute for Communicable Diseases. Courtesy #DStv403 - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.